{"id": "1377059641703534694", "channel_id": "1377059641703534694", "type": 0, "author_id": "111382919502684160", "author_name": "foxblood13", "author_bot": false, "content": "20 times a day is a lot of time to put in front of players, I know no one is forced but many will. Even if each attempt took around 5 minutes it's still an hour and 40 minutes of playtime a day, for just the event.\n\nSupports being locked doesn't make sense this time around. During anniversary event there was no limit to how much you could grind, so it made sense.  If locking them out continues in the future consider having them used once a day instead. Right now we're encouraged to add at least 140 players we will never interact with again, only to lose track of who they are and what character they used. \n\nThe support menu UI really needs filtering options as well, as I don't feel like scrolling through a ton of people I added the first time to find a character.", "timestamp": "2025-05-27T23:03:23.113000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-05-28T01:07:32.839000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "💯", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1377059641703534694", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "1.5 Event Grind", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
